ChEMBL_Assay_Description: Inhibition of recombinant human GSK-3beta using phosphorylated polypeptide as substrate incubated for 30 mins in presence of ATP by kinase-glo luminescence assay
Inhibition of recombinant human GSK-3beta using phosphorylated polypeptide as substrate incubated for 30 mins in presence of ATP by kinase-glo luminescence assay

Inhibition of P-gp mediated efflux in human Caco-2 cells assessed as increase in calcein-mediated intracellular fluorescence intensity at 10 uM preincubated for 30 mins followed by calcein-AM addition and measured after 30 mins by multimode plate reader analysis
